      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAI MONDO (1) after placing third here two runs back finished fifth of 12 over 1200m at this track last start when after leading into the turn was swamped late. Has a solid record at this distance and jumping from the inside gate will find the lead easily enough and racing over 150m less should prove hard to roll. WAX ON WAX OFF (6) after making a poor beginning recovered well to race in behind the speed and battled on well to finish a close fourth of 13 last time out over 1200m at this track. He won his maiden race here three runs back over today's distance and dropping down 2.5kg in weight looks well placed to return to winning form. OUR EAGLE ROCK (2) resumes from a spell and having won fresh-up last prep over 1100m at this track is well worth considering. Having his first run for a new stable and should be ready to fire having had the benefit of a recent trial run over 850m at Sunshine Coast Inner Track. KRACKACAN (3) is resuming today but will be fitter for a recent trial.",
